read

public int read(java.io.DataInput dataInput)
         throws java.io.IOException
Read the (integer) count and count bytes from the data input, adding to the end of this instance.

If there will not be enough memory to read the bytes, then they will not be read and the return value will be the negative of the count.

Returns:
the number of bytes read.
Throws:
java.io.IOException
